# Edge-function secrets — LOCAL DEV template.
#
# Copy to `supabase/functions/.env` (gitignored) and fill OPENROUTER_API_KEY, then run:
#   supabase functions serve agent-chat compose-view --env-file supabase/functions/.env --no-verify-jwt
# See docs/environments.md → "Edge Functions (local dev + prod deploy)".
#
# NEVER commit the filled `.env`. In PROD these are set with `supabase secrets set`, not a file.

# REQUIRED — the LLM key the agent-chat / compose-view deputies call OpenRouter with.
# NFR-AR-SEC-001: function secret only; never the client, never committed.
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# AUTO-INJECTED by the Supabase runtime for both `functions serve` (local) and deployed
# functions — you do NOT need to set these locally; listed for reference only.
# SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<local anon key from `supabase status`>
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=<local service-role key from `supabase status`>
AGENT_MODEL_DEFAULT=deepseek/deepseek-v4-flash
AGENT_MODEL_COMPOSE=

# Backend routing policy for the pinned model on OpenRouter (providerPolicyFromEnv). Default = the
# NO-TRAIN fallback tier: green (no-retain) DeepInfra -> DigitalOcean first, then retain-but-not-train
# hosts by jurisdiction+speed (GMICloud US -> Baidu/StreamLake/Alibaba CN -> DeepSeek last), with
# `only` HARD-restricting routing to that set so a fallback never lands on a training host. All
# optional. Trade privacy<->latency<->cache WITHOUT a code deploy. See
# docs/plans/2026-07-09-agent-model-cost-optimization.md.
# ⚠ VERIFY the provider slugs against openrouter.ai/<model>/providers before a PROD deploy — a wrong
#   slug in AGENT_PROVIDER_ONLY silently drops that host (set the verified list here, no redeploy).
#   AGENT_PROVIDER_ORDER=deepinfra,digitalocean,gmicloud,baidu,streamlake,alibaba,deepseek
#   AGENT_PROVIDER_ONLY=<same list>   # hard allow-list; fails SAFE — unset/empty keeps the no-train
#                                     # default. Disable ONLY with the explicit sentinel '*' (warns;
#                                     # data may then reach training backends).
#   AGENT_PROVIDER_IGNORE=            # comma slugs to never route to
#   AGENT_PROVIDER_SORT=             # throughput|price|latency (rank within the allow-list)
#   AGENT_PROVIDER_ALLOW_FALLBACKS= # 'false' to disable fallbacks (default: enabled)
#   AGENT_PROVIDER_DATA_COLLECTION= # 'deny' = green-only (no retention) | 'allow' (default: unset)
# AGENT_PROVIDER_ORDER=
# AGENT_PROVIDER_ONLY=
# AGENT_PROVIDER_IGNORE=
# AGENT_PROVIDER_SORT=
# AGENT_PROVIDER_ALLOW_FALLBACKS=
# AGENT_PROVIDER_DATA_COLLECTION=

# Transcript compaction — token-budget shrink of the replayed transcript sent to the model each
# round (old tool-result bodies past the recency window become a marker; system prefix + all
# reasoning text preserved). Input-only; never persisted. All optional — unset = tuned defaults.
#   AGENT_COMPACTION_TRIGGER_CHARS=24000   # compact only above this size; 0 DISABLES compaction
#   AGENT_COMPACTION_RECENT_MESSAGES=6     # trailing messages kept verbatim (~last 3 turns)
#   AGENT_COMPACTION_MAX_TOOL_CHARS=800    # older tool body over this → compacted
# AGENT_COMPACTION_TRIGGER_CHARS=
# AGENT_COMPACTION_RECENT_MESSAGES=
# AGENT_COMPACTION_MAX_TOOL_CHARS=

# AUDIT-M4: CORS allow-origin for agent-chat/compose-view. Unset ⇒ '*' (local dev).
# Prod: set to the deployed SPA origin, e.g. https://pmo-bfb.pages.dev
# AGENT_ALLOWED_ORIGIN=

# EXTERNAL_CONNECT_ENABLED — operator break-glass kill-switch for ClickUp / ERPNext execution.
# Default is ENABLED when unset, empty, or unrecognised — the per-org binding, not this flag,
# decides whether a given org syncs. This exists ONLY as an operator break-glass.
# DISABLE is deliberately liberal: `false`, `0`, `off`, `no`, or `disabled` (case-insensitive,
# whitespace-tolerant) ALL stop external execution everywhere. That asymmetry is intentional —
# the catastrophic failure mode for a break-glass control is an operator typing a reasonable
# false-y value under incident pressure, believing it stopped, while it keeps writing.
# In PROD this is a Supabase FUNCTION SECRET; set `EXTERNAL_CONNECT_ENABLED=false` only
# during an operator incident stop (NOT in a .env file).
# EXTERNAL_CONNECT_ENABLED=
